<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="270">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="270">Body narrowly elongate (Figs 1-6, 9-12) (broader in subalatus group, Figs 7-8); glabrous dorsally; color ranging from light to dark reddish-brown, often with yellow and/or piceous markings on elytra. Surface varying from smooth, shining, with very fine microsculpture (visible only under high magnification) to dull with dense, moderately fine, visible microsculpture. Length 6-13 mm.</paragraph>
